                            <comment id="13551901" author="davsclaus" created="Sat, 12 Jan 2013 12:32:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is already possible. You can configure a custom uri resolver on the component / endpoint.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.apache.org/xslt&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.apache.org/xslt&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;See this unit test in the source code: XsltCustomizeURIResolverTest&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="13551904" author="davsclaus" created="Sat, 12 Jan 2013 12:37:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah yeah the xslt endpoint loads the resource the 1st time without the customer resolver. Lets fix that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13551933" author="davsclaus" created="Sat, 12 Jan 2013 14:37:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting. Now the uri resolver is always used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13552475" author="t.gueldner" created="Mon, 14 Jan 2013 07:25:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are really fast. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will try it next time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
